FT  21 SEP 92 / International Company News: Omron slashes profits forecast
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By STEVEN BUTLER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TOKYO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
A DECLINE in Japanese companies' capital spending has forced Omron, the
electronic control equipment manufacturer, to slash its parent company
profits forecast, writes Steven Butler in Tokyo. Omron expects pre-tax
profits of Y7.0bn (Dollars 56m) in the 12 months to March, compared with
Y13.55bn the year before.
