the benefits of the company's cost reduction programme, and a lower tax
charge due to losses from previous years.
Total retail sales were 3.6 per cent lower than forecast at NZDollars
1.003bn, largely due to a slow recovery in the Auckland market. Mr Sadler
said growth would come from new stores throughout the North Island over the
coming months.
