FT  21 SEP 92 / UK Company News: GT Venture Invest net assets ahead
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
GT Venture Investment Company saw its basic net asset value increase from
144p to 146.2p over the 12 months to June 30. Diluted assets improved from
137.8p to 139.7p.
Net profits were Pounds 438,000 (Pounds 468,000) for earnings per share of
3.01p (3.2p). A single unchanged final dividend of 2.5p is proposed.
The trust has reached agreement with holders of its outstanding Pounds 18.4m
nominal of convertible unsecured loan stock 1999 to redeem the stock at a
significant discount to the nominal amount plus accrued premium totalling
Pounds 20.2m.
Holders have agreed to cancellation of conversion rights and interest will
become payable annually instead of being rolled up. As a consequence the
company warned that there would have to a substantial reduction in future
dividend payments.
The company is planning to change its name to Pantheon International
Participations.
