FT  21 SEP 92 / Trawlers get protection
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A FISHERIES protection vessel was standing off the Scilly Isles yesterday
after reports of more clashes between British and French trawlers in
disputed fishing grounds.
The Ministry of Defence said the fisheries protection vessel HMS Shetland
sailed to the area after the reports, but found no sign of French trawlers.
Falmouth Coastguards and the Ministry of Agriculture, Fisheries and Food
both confirmed that Cornish trawlers reported yesterday that French trawlers
were sailing close to the nets of British boats off the Scilly Isles.
They could not confirm reports that one British trawler's nets were
destroyed by the French trawler L'Arche, the same vessel involved in clashes
in June.
In those incidents, involving several trawlers from Newlyn and the Brittany
port of Concarneau, the Cornish fishermen's nets suffered Pounds 15,000 of
damage.
