FT  21 SEP 92 / Commander George Churchill-Coleman to be replaced by
Commander David Tucker
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
COMMANDER George Churchill-Coleman, head of Scotland Yard's anti-terrorist
branch for seven years, is to be replaced by Commander David Tucker, the
Metropolitan Police commissioner said yesterday.
Sir Peter Imbert said the move was one of a number involving senior officers
in the Metropolitan Police. Mr Tucker, at present head of the force's
criminal intelligence branch, takes over from Mr Churchill-Coleman against a
background of reports of the government's impatience with the anti-terrorist
squad's failure to prevent IRA attacks on the mainland.
Mr Kenneth Clarke, home secretary, recently said MI5 was to take over the
primary responsibility for gathering intelligence about IRA terrorism on
mainland Britain. Scotland Yard's anti-terrorist branch, which deals with
the investigation of IRA incidents and the subsequent preparation of
evidence, was unaffected operationally by the move.
